x4freetext: 14UD BARC-TIFR Pelletron-Linac
accelerator
124Sn target of thickness 2.47 +/- 0.4 mg/cm2 used
for online gamma measurement.
124Sn having thickness in the range of 1.5-4.0 mg/cm2
for offline gamma measurement.
Two Compton suppressed clover detectors were
placed at a distance of 25 cm from the target center,
one at 125 deg, for absolute cross-section estimation
of various reaction channels, and the other at 90 deg,
for identification of unshifted gamma lines.
A monitor detector (=500 um) was placed at 30
deg. It was used in the ER cross section estimation
using measured elastic (Rutherford) scattering cross
section.
The off-line gamma ray counting was done using
HPGe detector. The energy calibration and efficiency
of the detector were measured by calibrated
radioactive 152Eu, 133Ba and 241Am sources.
The beam energies were corrected for the loss at half
the target thickness

systematic uncertainties arises due to beam current,
target thickness, detector efficiency and extraction of
gamma-ray yield.
